author: Bianca Giulione
title: Watch Desiigner Get a Bootleg Kanye Vinyl from Nardwuar
text:
Doot Doola Doot Do! Desiigner is the latest artist to be interviewed by Canadian icon and Human Serviette Nardwuar. A career milestone for any musician, Desiigner took time out of his busy SXSW schedule in Austin last week for a chat with the infamous music journalist. In true Nardwuar fashion, he came bearing insanely well-researched gifts for the American rapper and alien – including a record from 1963 by Desiigner’s grandfather Guitar Crusher, who greatly impacted his love for music, a The Life of Pablo bootleg vinyl, and a Rush Hour 2 soundtrack since Nardwuar managed to dig up his obsession with Jackie Chan.
Here's a *new* interview i did with Desiigner at @sxsw 2017 in Austin, Texas ! Doot doo ! https://t.co/0s6kLBmEEY pic.twitter.com/w9f4oyPeVw 
— Nardwuar (@nardwuar) March 20, 2017 

In addition to being interviewed by the most well prepared and generous journalist in the world, Desiigner just casually announced he will be collaborating with adidas while sneaker shopping, and will probably drop a video for his latest single “Outlet” very soon if the tweet below is any indication. With all this going on, it’s clear The Life of Desiigner isn’t slowing down anytime soon.
OUTLET VIDEO 💯💯💪🏾💪🏾🔥🔥🔥
— Desiigner (@LifeOfDesiigner) March 19, 2017
